2.3 Orginizing sample information

# create sample names that begins from 12th position of colnames to end of the colnames using substring
samplenames <- substring(colnames(x), 12, nchar(colnames(x)))
samplenames
## [1] "10_6_5_11" "9_6_5_11"  "purep53"   "JMS8-2"    "JMS8-3"    "JMS8-4"   
## [7] "JMS8-5"    "JMS9-P7c"  "JMS9-P8c"
colnames(x) <- samplenames              # replace the colnames with the samplenames

group <- as.factor(c("LP", "ML", "Basal", "Basal", "ML", "LP", 
                     "Basal", "ML", "LP"))    # grouped the cell types as a factor and 3                                                  different levels 
x$samples$group <- group             # x is a large DGEList that include samples                                                and counts. Samples also, include 4 different columns                                       (files, group, lib,size, norm.factor). The group                                            factor I created is assigned to the group column here.

lane <- as.factor(rep(c("L004","L006","L008"), c(3,4,2)))
# The number of reads in each lane in the next-generation sequencing is different. Create lane as a factor that includes 3 different types 1st repeated 3 times, 2nd repeated 4 times, and 3rd repeated 2 times.

x$samples$lane <- lane     # add the lane factor as a 5 column in x$samples.

x$samples

2.4 Orginizing gene annotations

  • Select function is coming from AnnotationDbi.
geneid <- rownames(x)      # gene id information is found rownames of x.

genes <- select(Mus.musculus, keys=geneid, columns=c("SYMBOL", "TXCHROM"), 
                keytype="ENTREZID")
## 'select()' returned 1:many mapping between keys and columns
# Gene information is taken from mus.musculus. Data mapped to gene id contains 3 columns. SYMBOL is the symbol for genes. TXCHROM is the location of the genes on the chromosome. If the matched key type is ENTREZID, it is the same as the id.
head(genes)

3.2 Removing lowly-expressed genes

# Find 0 count. True means that count is 0. 
table(rowSums(x$counts==0)==9)  # 19% of genes are never expressed
## 
## FALSE  TRUE 
## 22026  5153
keep.exprs <- filterByExpr(x, group=group)    # filter the counts according to exp.

sum(keep.exprs)     # gives a new gene (row) size after the filtering
## [1] 16624
x <- x[keep.exprs,, keep.lib.sizes=FALSE]     # select all columns(,,) and keep.lib.sizes=FALSE because must be recalculate according to new exp. data

dim(x)
## [1] 16624     9

3.4 Unsupervised clustering of samples

library(RColorBrewer)

lcpm <- cpm(x, log=TRUE)
par(mfrow=c(1,2))
col.group <- group
levels(col.group) <-  brewer.pal(nlevels(col.group), "Set1")
col.group <- as.character(col.group)
col.lane <- lane
levels(col.lane) <-  brewer.pal(nlevels(col.lane), "Set2")
col.lane <- as.character(col.lane)
plotMDS(lcpm, labels=group, col=col.group)
title(main="A. Sample groups")
plotMDS(lcpm, labels=lane, col=col.lane, dim=c(3,4))
title(main="B. Sequencing lanes")

## Interactive unsupervised clustering

# Create a folder in a workspace include that interactive MDS plot html.
glMDSPlot(lcpm, labels=paste(group, lane, sep="_"),

design <- model.matrix(~0+group+lane)  # 0 means intercept is 0.

colnames(design) <- gsub("group", "", colnames(design))     # makes more readable

   LPvsML = LP - ML,

4.4 Fitting linear models for comparisons of interest

vfit <- lmFit(v, design)

vfit <- contrasts.fit(vfit, contrasts=contr.matrix)

efit <- eBayes(vfit)

plotSA(efit, main="Final model: Mean-variance trend")

4.5 Examining the number of DE genes

summary(decideTests(efit))
##        BasalvsLP BasalvsML LPvsML
## Down        4648      4927   3135
## NotSig      7113      7026  10972
## Up          4863      4671   2517
tfit <- treat(vfit, lfc=1) # 2 fold up/downregulation threshold

dt <- decideTests(tfit)

summary(dt)

9.8 Heatmap of top DE genes

library(gplots)

basal.vs.lp.topgenes <- basal.vs.lp$ENTREZID[1:100]

i <- which(v$genes$ENTREZID %in% basal.vs.lp.topgenes)

mycol <- colorpanel(1000,"blue","white","red")

heatmap.2(lcpm[i,], scale="row",
   labRow=v$genes$SYMBOL[i], labCol=group, 
   col=mycol, trace="none", density.info="none", 
   margin=c(8,6), lhei=c(2,10),
   dendrogram="column")
